Notes for Eclipse with TRUST (21/07/2015)
-----------------------------------------

######################################
# Create a project to browse sources #
######################################

Download
========
> Go to the website of the Eclipse Foundation: http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
> Select Eclipse for Parallel Application Developers Linux 64 Bit
> Download the eclipse-parallel-luna-SR2-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz file in your directory

Installation
============
> cd /export/home/login
> gunzip eclipse-parallel-luna-SR2-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz
> tar xvf eclipse-parallel-luna-SR2-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar
> rm  eclipse-parallel-luna-SR2-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar
> cd eclipse

Configuration
=============
> Change the end of the eclipse.ini file
> vi eclipse.ini
-Dhelp.lucene.tokenizer=standard
-XX:PermSize=256m
-XX:MaxPermSize=1024m
-XX:+UseParallelGC
-Xmn256m
-Xss2m
-Xms512m
-Xmx2048m
-server

Launching
=========
> ./eclipse &
> Workspace: /export/home/login/eclipse/workspace 
  => OK
  => Welcome: close X
> File/New/C++ Project 
  => Profect name: TRUST_X.Y.Z
  => Use default location
  => Project type: Executable/Empty Project
  => Toolchains: Linux GCC
  => Finish
> Project Explorer
  Right click TRUST_X-Y-Z/Import...
  => General/File System
  => Next 
  => From directory: /data/tmpletr/triou/installations/TRUST_X.Y.Z/OS_machine/TRUST_X.Y.Z/src
  => Select All  
  => Into folder: TRUST_X.Y.Z
  => Advanced: check Create links in workspace
  =>           not check Create virtual folders
  => Finish 
> Project Explorer
  Right click TRUST_X.Y.Z/Properties
  => Builders: not check CDT Builder => OK
  => OK
  => Wait to have 100% at the bottom right corner of the window.
> File/Exit


######################################
# Launch a calculation in debug mode #
######################################

Configuration
============= 
> cd eclipse
> source /data/tmpletr/triou/installations/TRUST_X.Y.Z/OS_machine/TRUST_X.Y.Z/env/env_TRUST.sh
> ./eclipse &
> Project Explorer
  Right click TRUST_X.Y.Z/Debug As/Debug configurarions...
  => Select C/C++ Application
  => Press the 'New' button to create a configuration of the selected type
  => Main: C/C++ Application:  /data/tmpletr/triou/installations/TRUST_X.Y.Z/OS_machine/TRUST_X.Y.Z/exec/TRUST_mpi
  => Arguments: not check Use default working directory
  => Debugger: Main options GDB debugger: replace gdb by /usr/bin/gdb
  => Close => Save Changes Yes

View debug
==========
> Window/Open Perspective/Debug
  => New button at the top right of the window: view Debug side view C/C++

Case selection
==============
> Run/Debug configurations
  => Select C/C++ application TRUST_X.Y.Z Debug
  => Arguments: Program arguments: datafile               (for example Cx)
  =>            Working directoty: /export/home/login/... (for example /export/home/login/Cx : folder of Cx test case in your home-directories)
  => Close => Save Changes Yes

Launching
=========
> Run/Debog (F11)         (Wait to have 100% on the bottom right corner of the window)
> Run/Resume (F8)
> Run/Terminate (Ctrl+F2)
> File/Exit

